TVDB-API v0.21

This module implements a perl module for the API detailed at

    http://thetvdb.com/wiki/index.php/Programmers_API

It allows access to the information about TV shows stored at

    http://thetvdb.com/

To use it you will first have to register for an apikey from thetvdb.

    http://thetvdb.com/?tab=apiregister

A different apikey is required per application which accesses thetvdb api.

This modules requires the following extra perl modules:

    Compress::Zlib
    DBM::Deep
    Debug::Simple
    IO::Uncompress::Unzip
    LWP
    XML::Simple

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc TVDB::API

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=TVDB-API

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/TVDB-API

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/TVDB-API

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/TVDB-API


